                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1118">Addai (Aday) was one of the 72 apostles
          commissioned by Jesus to be a missionary. Aday was ordained by <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1118">Thomas</persName> to travel to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName>, and he cured King Abgar's foot.
          The conversion of Edessa was attributed to his missionary activity and described in the
          Teaching of Addai.</note>
